               <persName id="t18140420-56-person563">
                  Edward 
                  Brazely
               <interp inst="t18140420-56-person563" type="surname" value="Brazely"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18140420-56-person563" type="given" value="Edward"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18140420-56-person563" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            's box was searched, at Mr. Moody's, at the time the piece of Irish linen was found that Mr. Bartrop noticed to be his.</p>
               <p>Q. Do you know anything of 
               <persName id="t18140420-56-person564">
                  Edward 
                  Brazely
               <interp inst="t18140420-56-person564" type="surname" value="Brazely"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18140420-56-person564" type="given" value="Edward"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18140420-56-person564" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             - A. Not in the least; I have every reason to believe he was not in my house on the night these pieces of Irish linen were brought. A servant of mine is here to testify he was not; his name is 
               <persName id="t18140420-56-person565">
                  Thomas 
                  Pickering
               <interp inst="t18140420-56-person565" type="surname" value="Pickering"></interp>
