               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18140420-56-person570">
                  WILLIAM 
                  READ
               <interp inst="t18140420-56-person570" type="surname" value="READ"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18140420-56-person570" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18140420-56-person570" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer of Hatton Garden office. This piece of Irish linen was given into my custody by Blake, the constable; I have had it ever since; I now produce it.</p>
               <p>Prosecutor. It is the property of me and my partner; it is marked 11, O W; it is my marking.</p>
               <p>Edward Brazely's Defence. I am innocent of this charge. My wife brought these things to me, and told me to lock them up in my box at Mr. Moody's. On Sunday she sent the key to me; she said, I might want the key, as they would search the box; every thing in my box she had bought; it was safe to let the box be examined.</p>
               <p>Susannah Brazely's Defence. I did not scour the room.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18140420-56-verdict300" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18140420-56-verdict300" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               NOT GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>Second Middlesex jury, before Mr. Justice Chambre.</p>
